     Cayley graphs


        Draws the right Cayley graph of a finite monoid or semigroup S.





        This function is a synonym of 
.



For example, the command DrawCayleyGraph(b21); would produce the following image
(where state i represents the element Elements(S)[i], the neutral element is
coloured in "light blue" and all other idempotents are coloured in "light coral"):

        \begin{center}
        \includegraphics[width=0.4\textwidth]{images/cgb21.png}
        \end{center}


      <br><center><img src="images/cgb21.png"></center><br>




        This function computes the dot code that is used by the previous function and can also be used by the reader in some independent way.









